{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"56c67b8e-8b15-4316-98a0-1b2319f9db46","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, arguments after `--` are passed directly to MTP. The equivalent command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/**/*[Category=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/**/*[Category=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test projects):\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` (or `Microsoft.CodeCoverage`)\n\n**Required project property** (in `Directory.Build.props` or each test `.csproj`):\n```xml\n<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cf4212f9-1635-4a31-828b-327faa868e4c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` (using Microsoft.CodeCoverage)\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith MTP, there are two execution paths: running through `dotnet test` as a wrapper, or invoking the test executable directly. In .NET 9+, `dotnet test` has native MTP support, but with .NET 8 you'll typically need to run the test executable directly or use `dotnet run` to invoke it.\n\nFor .NET 8 projects using MTP through `dotnet test`, you can enable it via the `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` project setting, then pass MTP arguments after the `--` separator. I'm working through a practical example showing how to run tests with filtering, coverage collection, and diagnostic dumps using this approach. I need to clarify the MTP filter syntax situation. MTP doesn't natively support VSTest's `--filter` syntax unless you add the VSTestBridge package for backward compatibility, so the proper approach is using `--treenode-filter` with the MTP-specific syntax. Let me show the practical command with the correct MTP arguments for filtering by category, along with the other options like trx reporting, coverage collection, and dump settings.\n\nWriting the command example... Completing the command with hangdump options and the necessary package dependencies for each feature in the MTP migration.","outputTokens":1810,"requestId":"67C3:2636C7:2B14AA6:2F6093B:69FD3500"},"id":"f98b18bb-140e-4ee3-aca9-b3801ad87bf1","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:58:07.309Z","parentId":"3740dfaa-9e41-42f7-ad28-af62ca18a36c"}
